		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Perhaps left thumb swipe to start moving, left thumb tap to stop</div><br />That would be terrible for quick/fine movement. Couldn't directions be detected by the relative displacement from the start of the touch? To stop you just lift your thumb. Much more similar to what you'd do with a common controller (the only real difference is that you have to touch the center first), and you can still do it without looking.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">right thumb swipe up to jump, and right thumb tap to attack?</div><br />That sounds reasonable.

		

		</td>
